# HPAI Risk Modelling

A reproducible framework for modelling Highly Pathogenic Avian Influenza (HPAI) risk across poultry and wild bird populations.

## Objectives

- Predict outbreak risk
- Identify environmental drivers
- Generate spatial risk maps
- Support surveillance planning
- Evaluate intervention scenarios

## Data Sources

- Poultry outbreak records
- Wild bird surveillance
- Weather data
- Land-use data
- Wetland distribution
- Poultry density
- Bird migration routes

## Modelling Approaches

- Logistic Regression
- Random Forest
- XGBoost
- Bayesian Hierarchical Models
- Spatio-temporal Models

